-- allium: 3
-- specs/cuda-native-dispatch/single_threaded_dispatch.allium
--
-- Status: PLACEHOLDER. Bound by PHASE_CUDA_NATIVE_DISPATCH.md
-- commit C1 (replace ggml_backend_sched_compute_splits openmp
-- parallel block with single-threaded multi-backend iteration).
--
-- Scope: the new ggml_backend_sched_compute_splits, which runs on
-- exactly one host thread per process lifetime. NO openmp parallel
-- region, NO std::barrier fallback, NO per-backend worker threads.
-- Cross-backend dependencies are expressed as cudaEvent record/wait
-- pairs on per-backend CUDA streams, not host-side barriers.
--
-- Why this spec exists: PD1 (PHASE_CUDA_NATIVE_DISPATCH.md §10)
-- identified four CUDA-context shared fields that race under
-- multi-thread eval entry (cuda_graphs map, pools[device],
-- cublas_handles[device], streams[device][n] lazy-creates). The
-- structural fix is to eliminate concurrent host-side context
-- access by construction. This spec binds that property.
--
-- The dispatch model is CUDA-idiomatic: host enqueues all kernels
-- async on per-backend streams; the CUDA driver schedules them
-- concurrently across devices; cross-device deps are events; per-
-- token replay is a single cudaGraphLaunch over the captured graph.
--
-- Includes:
--   - External entity for the sched object
--     (ggml_backend_sched_t, SplitSequence, BackendStream).
--   - Contracts for ComputeSplits — must run on one host thread,
--     must enqueue every split's eval on the owning backend's
--     stream, must establish event-chain dependencies between
--     cross-backend producer/consumer pairs.
--   - Contracts for EventChain — every cross-backend read has a
--     matching producer cudaEventRecord that precedes it.
--
-- CODE REFS (paths from /home/dconnolly/yarn-agentic):
